 # AGENTS.md
 
-## Repository nature
+## Project Overview
 
-This is a **documentation-only knowledge base**, not a software project. There is no source code, no build system, no test suite, no linter, no package manager, and **no git repository initialized**. Do not look for or suggest running `build`/`test`/`lint`/`typecheck` commands, and do not propose git workflows (commit, branch, PR) unless the user first initializes git.
+This is a Pi Coding Agent project for CSP (Aptar active packaging) sales lead discovery. The agent scrapes regulatory and clinical trial data, matches customer profiles, and generates Markdown lead reports.
 
-## Content domain & language
+## LLM Configuration
 
-All content is written in **Simplified Chinese** and covers pharmaceutical packaging and drug-impurity topics:
+- Provider: Qwen (閫氫箟鍗冮棶) via DashScope OpenAI-compatible API
+- Models: `qwen-max` for complex reasoning (report generation), `qwen-plus` for routine tasks
+- Config: `config/models.json` 鈫?mounted to `/root/.pi/agent/models.json` in Docker
+- API key: `DASHSCOPE_API_KEY` environment variable
 
-- `CSP.md` 鈥?Comparative analysis of Aptar CSP active packaging technologies (Activ-Vial庐, Activ-Film庐, Activ-Blister庐, 3-Phase Activ-Polymer鈩? Activ-Sachet庐, custom adsorbents). Contains performance data tables, regulatory status, cost/scalability notes, case studies, and a numbered source list with external URLs.
-- `20260616_6鏈堜笂鏂颁簹纭濊兒鑽墿鍒嗘瀽鏉傝川.md` 鈥?USP Pharmaceutical Analytical Impurities (PAI) nitrosamine series update. Lists newly released nitrosamine impurities (Chinese/English name, USP catalog number, CAS) and a roster of ~100 affected active pharmaceutical ingredients.
+## Project Structure
 
-When editing, preserve the bilingual (Chinese name + English name) conventions and the existing table structures, since they mirror USP/Aptar reference formats.
+- `skills/browser_executor/` 鈥?Generic Playwright browser automation tool (shared across all scenarios)
+- `scenarios/` 鈥?Business scenario skills (nitrosamine, probiotics, IVD, etc.)
+- `prompts/` 鈥?Pi prompt templates (entry points like `/lead-scan`)
+- `config/` 鈥?Cached data and model configuration
+- `output/` 鈥?Generated reports and run snapshots
 
-## File naming convention
+## Key Conventions
 
-Time-sensitive update notes use a `YYYYMMDD_` date prefix (e.g. `20260616_...`). Topical reference documents (e.g. `CSP.md`) use a short uppercase mnemonic with no date. Follow this convention when adding new files: date-prefixed for periodic updates, plain mnemonic for standing reference material.
-
-## Citations & sources
-
-`CSP.md` ends with a numbered `[n]` source list of external URLs, and inline references use the same `[n]` markers. When adding claims that rely on external data, append a new numbered source entry and cite it inline; do not leave bare `銆?..銆慲 placeholders (a few exist in the current file and should be replaced with real sources when available).
